<HEADLINE>
VALDES WASHED OUT IN DEBUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH _ Right-hander Ismael Valdes' return to the Los
Angeles Dodgers was washed away after 11 pitches and two
baserunners in Pittsburgh as rain forced the cancellation of
Monday's series opener against the Pirates at Three Rivers Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   The game was rescheduled as part of a doubleheader today
beginning at 2:05 p.m. Dodgers Lefty Carlos Perez will pitch the
first game against Pittsburgh lefty Jimmy Anderson. Valdes will
start the second game and oppose right-hander Bronson Arroyo.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ismael said he'd be all right, so he'll throw the second
game,'' Dodgers manager Davey Johnson. ``I won't be able to get as
much out of him but hopefully four or five innings. The other
option would have been to bring (Darren) Dreifort back on three.''
</P>
<P>
   Pittsburgh starter Jose Silva retired Devon White, Mark
Grudzielanek and Gary Sheffield in order in the top of the first,
but Valdes was in trouble to begin the bottom of the inning. He
walked Warren Morris to lead off and Jason Kendall singled to
right.
</P>
<P>
   However, heavy rains and thunderstorms stopped the game, and
after one hour, 45 minutes, the game was called. It's the first day
the Dodgers had off since the All-Star break, but it sets up a
grueling 24 hours with Wednesday's afternoon game.
</P>
</TEXT>
