</P>
<P>
   But no, the real question is much simpler: why aren't non-Jewish
and non-Arab Americans saying these things?
</P>
<P>
   Why aren't ``ordinary'' Americans _ i.e., those without a stake
in the Middle East _ asking these questions?
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, if the Boston Globe's own journalists had reported what
Ron told the paper's readers, their dispatches would have remained
unpublished.
</P>
<P>
   Rafeedie and Ron should take a bow: a Palestinian and an Israeli
didn't worry that they were the only people walking down the path
of truth.
</P>
<P>
   But why does it take such courage in America to tell the truth
about the Middle East? &QL; 
