<P>
   GOPKOLBE (Philadelphia) - Rep. Jim Kolbe, R-Ariz., has always
been reserved about his sexual orientation, so it's a bit of a
surprise that he consented to be publicly honored Tuesday at the
convention by the Log Cabin Republicans, a gay political group that
will hold a reception for him. He'll also address the convention on
foreign policy - but there may be controversy. The word is at least
a dozen of the Texas delegates are planning a silent walkout to
protest the fact that he is gay. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move in
the ``A'' category.
</P>
