<P>
   TECH-METRICOM _ ATLANTA _ Ricochet _ Metricom's high-speed,
wireless connection to laptops launches this week. Metricom has
placed about 2,700 small transmitters on phone poles throughout
metro Atlanta. The idea is to give a mobile worker _ professional
or technician _ constant Internet connection. (The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TECH-LINKTEL _ ATLANTA _ LinkTel offers a service that lets
people access the Net and get email while they are otherwise stuck:
their car is being serviced, they are waiting for a table at a
restaurant, etc. Company is, appropriately, making the switch from
pay phones to public Net access. (The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
