   TV-AMERICANHIGH _ Fox rolls out American High, the latest
reality show with a twist: This one followed a group of teens
through a Chicago-area high school during the '99-'00 school year.
Airs in two half-hour segments Wednesday against ``Big Brother's''
weekly life show on CBS. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-AUGUST _ August is the most excessive part of summer. Local
farmers, blessed with the best growing season in years, have
bounteous crops of corn and tomatoes, zucchini and beans, peaches
and berries, including a second harvest of raspberries on the
horizon. And there's more to come. There's enough to fill each page
of the calendar until September signals that the extravagance of
summer is fading. (Dayton Daily News). 26. WITH PHOTOS,
ILLUSTRATION AND PAGE LAYOUT.
</P>
