   SHAKESPEARE-STRATFORD (Stratford-Upon-Avon) _ Over the course of
the next year the Royal Shakespeare Company will present the eight
history plays in which Shakespeare depicts the upheaval of
15th-century England. Because the plays cover such closely related
historical events, seeing them together is an incomparably richer
experience than seeing them individually. It is also a rare one.
This is only the fifth time in a century that the feat has been
attempted in England, and no past attempt has been so complete or
intense. By Stephen Kinzer.
