<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors:
</P>
<P>
   Here's TheStreet.com column for TUESDAY, August 1, 2000.
</P>
<P>
   SWEET DEAL? MICROSOFT PRICES OPTIONS BELOW 70, by Adam Lashinsky
</P>
<P>
   In a departure from past policy, Microsoft priced its most
recent grant of stock options to employees on Monday, July 31. That
means that employees got options on tens of millions of shares at
69 13/16, Monday's closing stock price. That's a huge relief to the
Microsofties, who have seen the stock a lot higher recently.
</P>
<P>
   Also, why did the Corvis play on Comdisco _ buying shares in
Comdisco because the company owns a big chunk of Corvis' options _
work, only to come unraveled the day shares of Corvis began
trading?
</P>
<P>
   Slugged BC-THESTREETCOM-LASHINSKY-NYTSF
</P>
