</P>
<P>
   SOMALIA-REVIVE (Arta, Djibouti) _ About 2,000 ordinary Somalis,
along with most of their leaders, have been meeting in this
neighboring country since March, trying _ for the 13th time _ to
re-make Somalia, which collapsed in civil war in 1991. So far, they
have agreed on a national charter. Within the next week they expect
to have elected a three-year, 225-member national assembly. They
have picked a temporary capital, in the southern city of Baidoa.
And already, the campaign for the next president, to be elected
here by the assembly members, is in high gear. By Ian Fisher.
