   JAPAN-BANK (Tokyo) _ Softbank is scrapping a plan to sell shares
in units that are involved in electronic commerce, publishing,
online banking, insurance and software. The decision, which the
company said was aimed partly at keeping its tax bill low, comes
after analysts questioned whether the plan would make Softbank,
whose shares have fallen 70 percent this year, a less attractive
investment.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-ELECTRICITY (Sao Paulo) _ On the acute shortage of
electric power in Brazil, where nearly all electricity is provided
by hydro-electric plants. Because of low rainfall, the productivity
of those plants is threatened, and the problem is approaching what
some consider crisis levels. By Jennifer L. Rich.
