present a more familiar focus at their convention, that of the
party that embraces and promotes military strength. Tonight, the
podium will be dominated by war heroes: Gen. Norman Schwarzkopf,
former Sen. Bob Dole and Sen. John McCain. But the underlying
message is the same: The Republican Party under George W. Bush is
united behind a single message, relentlessly disciplined and
focused on taking the White House.
