 &QL; 
For the record &QL; 
In last week's Cook's Corner column, the recipe for
Chicken-Cranberry Molded Salad was missing the amount of
mayonnaise. It should be 1 cup. The corrected recipe follows.
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN-CRANBERRY MOLDED SALAD &QL; 
(Shared by Margaret Walsh, Van Nuys) &QL; 
CRANBERRY LAYER: &QL; 
1 package unflavored gelatin &QL; 
1/4 cup water &QL; 
2 (1-pound) cans whole cranberries &QL; 
1 (8-ounce) can crushed pineapple (1 cup) &QL; 
1/3 cup nuts &QL; 
CHICKEN LAYER: &QL; 
1 package unflavored gelatin &QL; 
1/4 cup water &QL; 
2 cups cooked cubed chicken &QL; 
3/4 cup chopped celery &QL; 
3 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley &QL; 
1 cup mayonnaise &QL; 
1/2 cup undiluted evaporated milk &QL; 
1 teaspoon Accent &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   For Cranberry Layer, soften gelatin in water. Dissolve over hot
water. Then add remaining Cranberry Layer ingredients. Turn into a
mold and chill until partially set.
</P>
<P>
   For Chicken Layer, soften gelatin in water. Dissolve over hot
water. Add remaining Chicken layer ingredients; mix well. Pour over
Cranberry Layer. Chill until set. Makes 6 to 8 servings. &QL; 
!hair!
</P>
