<P>
   CVN-NATIONAL-SECURITY (Philadelphia) _ Republicans devote the
second evening of their convention to drawing sharp distinctions
between their party and the Democrats on national security and
foreign policy. Scheduled speakers include Sen. John McCain of
Arizona; retired Army Gen. H. Norman Schwarzkopf, commander of
allied forces in the Persian Gulf War; 1996 GOP presidential
nominee Bob Dole; and Condoleeza Rice, a senior adviser to Texas
Gov. George W. Bush. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
