<HEADER>
A9627 &Cx1f; tad-z
r f BC-TECH-WORKGEAR0802-COX     08-01 0171
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-WORKGEAR0802-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    It's your world _ hang it up
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Probably considered low-tech but versatile
nonetheless is the good old-fashioned fridge magnet. More
importantly, a no-brainer-tech item in a high-tech office exudes a
certain savvy in less-is-more functionality. The central feature of
Magnalite Map Kits ($250 to $425; www.magzone.com) is the mountable
map, world or U.S., for use in a variety of applications, be it in
the boardroom, study hall or conference center. Kit components
include a 24-by-36 inch or 36-by-48 inch map board with a thin
metal lining, magnetic cardholders, write-on/wipe-off magnetic data
cards, and magnetic marker dots, vinyl letters and numbers. An
innovative, strategic planning tool as fully customizable as a map
can be. Plus it's eternally reusable _ or at least reusable until
the next tectonic shift sinks California.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
