<P>
   CANADA-MEDIA (Halifax, Nova Scotia) _ Israel ``Izzy' Asper, a
Winnipeg entrepreneur who already controls a hefty percentage of
Canada's TV and radio stations and is known for his liberal views,
acquires the country's biggest newspaper empire from conservative
Conrad Black. The $2.3 billion takeover leaves Asper in control of
some 148 newspapers, including the Ottawa Citizen and the Montreal
Gazette. By Colin Nickerson. 960 words. (i and f coding)
</P>
