his army again, should he want to? By Yvonne Abraham. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-BUSH (Harrisburg, Pa.) _ George W. Bush, who has long
pledged to rise above personal attacks in his presidential
campaign, uses some of his harshest language yet to ridicule his
opponent's administration, calling President Clinton ``desperate''
for getting involved in the race. By Anne E. Kornblut. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-CHENEY (Philadelphia) _ A week after George W. Bush asked
Dick Cheney to join him on the ticket, the campaign is still
getting used to having a second banana and Cheney is hustling to
reacquaint himself with a political world he once mastered. By Glen
Johnson. 1060 words.
