   VERIZON-STRIKE (Undated) _ In what analysts are calling a battle
between the old economy and the nation's emerging new economy, some
85,000 unionized Verizon Communications workers are threatening a
walkout that for, both sides, is a life-and-death struggle for
survival in the wireless age. By Diane E. Lewis. 900 words.
