period for the race for the U.S. Senate from Georgia. Story will
lead with ValuJet founder Lewis Jordan if he announces candidacy
today. The seat was previously held by Paul Coverdell, who died
unexpectedly recently. Gov. Roy Barnes appointed former Georgia
Gov. Zell Miller to serve Coverdell's term until a special election
for the seat in November. (Pruitt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
12.
