than 200 people who became entrapped by bedrails and mattresses
since 1985. Yet U.S. safety agencies are still debating whether to
take action beyond issuing warnings. The deaths continue. A Boca
Raton, Fla., nursing home is among those being sued. (Malone, Cox
News Service). 20.
