<P>
   TEXAS AT LARGE-CHAPMAN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Thirty years ago, in a wooded setting between Weslaco
and Mercedes, bird fanciers and conservationists moved their mobile
homes into a park where they could enjoy the wonders of nature. In
time, Lakeview Park became the winter home of nearly 270 annual
visitors to the Texas Rio Grande Valley. An additional 40 or so
families made it their year-round home. Now they all have to move;
tear up years of trees, plants and shrubs that have grown around
their mobile homes and leave the park. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has
moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
.MDNM/ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HUMOR-MEDICINE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Quackers, a hand puppet, Nurse Ducky and a
traveling band of merrymakers named the HaHaS have everybody in
stitches at Harris Methodist Southwest Hospital. For 20 years,
Marcy Graves (Nurse Ducky), nurses, therapists, technicians and
occasionally doctors, make the rounds of the hospital every
Wednesday, bringing laughter to patients. Fort Worth's version of
Dr. Patch Adams has even been invited by Adams to join his group of
clowns for a tour of China in September. By CAROLYN POIROT. Story
will move in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PET INSURANCE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ As employers across the country take notice of the
emotional connection between employees and their four-legged
companions, a growing number are including pet insurance in their
benefits package. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DREAM HOUSE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Polly Scheneker built her dream house, hired
notorious Hollywood designer William Haines to decorate, and then
invited Joan Crawford to come visit. The Fort Worth house with a
Hollywood past is for sale. By GAILE ROBINSON. Story has moved in
``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM PRESERVATION &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Shocking!'' ``An Abomination!'' These might be the
scathing reviews for Hollywood's record on preserving and restoring
its classic films. The last 10 years have seen a more enlightened
attitude toward salvaging the film industry's heritage of the last
100 years. But it may be a case of too little too late. By ANDREW
MARTON. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category.
(Accompanied by PRESERVATION-LOST FILMS.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO GAME-TENNIS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Aside from, like, pool and bowling, tennis is probably
one of the most difficult sports to reproduce for the video-game
