<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-01 19:17 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9739 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u t BC-TRAV-OZARKS-TIPS-HNS &LR;      08-01 0695
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAV-OZARKS-TIPS-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
TIPS FOR PLANNING YOUR TRIP TO LAKE OF THE OZARKS &HT;    By HARRY SHATTUCK
 &HT;    c.2000 Houston Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &UR; Planning:  &LR; Request a free 150-page vacation guide by writing
to the Lake of the Ozarks Convention and Visitor Bureau, P.O. Box
1498, Osage Beach, MO 65065. Call 800-386-5253. E-mail
locvbusmo.com. Access www.funlake.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   For a Missouri state map and brochures that include information
about attractions, events, lodging and dining statewide, call
800-877-1234 or access www.missouritourism.org.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; When to go:  &LR; Summer is peak season, and late spring or early
fall also are good times to visit. Some attractions close during
the winter. Daily high temperatures average 90.5 degrees in August
and 83.1 degrees in September. Nightly lows are in the 60s even in
summer.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Golf packages:  &LR; Resorts can recommend packages and book tee
times. Call 800-490-8474 to request a free Lake of the Ozarks Golf
Guide.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Boating tours:  &LR; Ninety-minute cruises aboard the Tropic Island
depart at 10 a.m. Tuesdays-Sundays from the Lodge of Four Seasons
marina. Cost is $12. Other times are available upon demand, and
charter excursions can be arranged. Call 573-348-0083, e-mail
infotropicislandcruises.com or access www.tropicislandcruises.com.
</P>
<P>
   The Lake of the Ozarks Convention and Visitors Bureau can
provide information about other excursions.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Fishing:  &LR; Licenses are required of all persons except Missouri
residents older than age 65 and anyone younger than age 16.
Nonresident license fees are $35; special licenses are available
for $5 a day. Daily and possession limits apply. For more
information, call the Missouri Department of Conservation at
573-751-4115 or write to P.O. Box 180, Jefferson City, MO 65102.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Other attractions: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Willmore Lodge, 1 Willmore Lane (U.S. 54 Business), Lake Ozark.
Call 800-451-4117.
</P>
<P>
   Bridal Cave, two miles north of Camdenton on Missouri 5. Guided
tours daily year-round. Call 573-346-2676, e-mail
infobridalcave.com or access www.bridalcave.com.
</P>
<P>
   Ha Ha Tonka State Park. Admission is free. Call 573-346-2986.
</P>
<P>
   Lake of the Ozarks State Park. Park admission is free, but a
small charge is assessed to enter Ozark Caverns. Call 573-346-2500.
</P>
<P>
   Jacob's Cave, State Road TT north of Gravois Mills. Call
573-378-4374.
</P>
<P>
   Factory Outlet Village, U.S. 54, Osage Beach. Call 573-348-2065.
</P>
<P>
   Big Surf Waterpark, and Big Shot Raceways and Fun Park, Highway
54 at Y Road, Linn Creek. Call 573-346-6111.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Lodging: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Marriott's Tan-Tar-A Resort, Golf Club and Spa, State Road KK,
Osage Beach. Call 800-826-8272. Access www.tan-tar-a.com.
</P>
<P>
   Lodge of Four Seasons, State Road HH, Lake Ozark. Call
800-843-5253. Access www.4seasonsresort.com.
</P>
<P>
   Country Club Hotel &AMP; Spa, Lake Ozark (State Road KK at Carol
Road). Call 800-964-6698. Access www.countryclubhotel.com.
</P>
<P>
   Holiday Inn Sunspree Resort, U.S. 54 Business, Lake Ozark. Call
800-532-3575.
</P>
<P>
   Forever Resorts (houseboat rentals), Missouri 5 at Niangua
Bridge, Camdenton. Call 800-255-5561 or access
www.foreverresorts.com.
</P>
<P>
   More than 25 campgrounds and/or RV parks are scattered
throughout the region. The Lake of the Ozarks Vacation Guide
provides complete information about each facility.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Dining  &LR; (call for hours, which vary by season, and to ask if
reservations are advised):
</P>
<P>
   Andre's, State Road HH, Lake Ozark. Call 573-365-2800.
</P>
<P>
   HK's Steak House, State Road HH (Lodge of Four Seasons), Lake
Ozark. Call 573-365-8509.
</P>
<P>
   Toledo's, State Road HH (Lodge of Four Seasons), Lake Ozark.
Call 573-365-8507.
</P>
<P>
   Windrose Restaurant, Marriott's Tan-Tar-A Resort, State Road KK,
Osage Beach. Call 573-348-3131.
</P>
<P>
   Country Club Restaurant, State Road HH and Carol Road. Call
573-964-2222.
</P>
<P>
   Kenilworth Restaurant, U.S. 54 near State Road KK, Osage Beach.
Call 573-348-4791.
</P>
<P>
   Kenilworth Bakery and Grill, U.S. 54 Business, Lake Ozark. Call
573-365-2300.
</P>
<P>
   Three Pigs Barbecue, Mill Creek Cove, Gravois Arm. Call
573-372-1700.
</P>
<P>
   Randy's Frozen Custard, U.S. 54, Osage Beach. Call 573-348-0711.
</P>
<P>
   X X X END OF STORY
</P>
<P>
   $$$
