<HEADLINE>
GAME-NIGHT TIPS:
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)   &HT;    c. 2000 Houston Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   1. Let each person bring his favorite game(s) and introduce it
to the group.
</P>
<P>
   2. Create a comfortable atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
   3. Munchies (popcorn, chips, cookies) are a necessity.
</P>
<P>
   4. Know the rules of your game ahead of time. You don't want to
introduce a forgotten rule during the middle of the game, thus
angering your fellow players.
</P>
<P>
   5. Feel free to use house rules if everyone agrees.
</P>
<P>
   6. Be open to new board games.
</P>
<P>
   7. Choose teams. It can add to the fun.
</P>
<P>
   8. If you're playing with friends, rotate game locations.
</P>
<P>
   9. Resist sidebar conversations that distract from the game.
</P>
<P>
   10. Be patient with other players.
</P>
<P>
   Sources: about.com and Hasbro
</P>
