<HEADLINE>
WORLD NEWS IN BRIEF 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EUROPE
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN: GAS PRICE STRIKE
</P>
<P>
   Motorists enraged by gasoline prices exceeding $4.80 a gallon
staged a rare protest by refusing to fill their gas tanks.
Organizers said they hoped to stage regular protests to urge the
government to lower taxes, which account for three-quarters of the
pump price of gasoline.
</P>
<P>
   ASIA
</P>
<P>
   PHILIPPINES: TRASH SURVIVORS SUE
</P>
<P>
   Survivors of the collapse of a mountain of garbage in the
capital, Manila, filed a class-action suit against local officials
and private waste contractors, accusing them of negligence. At
least 218 people _ and possibly hundreds more _ died when a
rain-soaked wall of garbage buried their shanties on July 10.
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA: BOMB KILLS THREE
</P>
<P>
   A powerful bomb at the residence of the Philippine ambassador in
the Indonesian capital, Jakarta, killed three people and injured at
least 21, including the ambassador. Muslim separatists in the
Philippines denied responsibility. A number of bombs linked to the
separatists have exploded recently in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA: ATTEMPTS TO FREE ACTOR
</P>
<P>
   A 10-year manhunt against the nation's most feared bandit was
suspended as authorities tried to negotiate the release of a
kidnapped movie icon, Rajkumar, taken prisoner by Veerappan, a
notorious murderer, poacher and smuggler who operates in the
forests of south India. S.M. Krishna, chief minister of the state
of Karnataka, said that the police do not want to do anything that
might further endanger Rajkumar.
</P>
<P>
   LAOS: NEW TERROR SCARE
</P>
<P>
   Residents reported that a bomb was found and defused at the
Vietnamese embassy in the Laotian capital, Vientiane. The latest
report in a series of bombings or attempted bombings, the discovery
came on Sunday, the same day that an explosive device was removed
from the Vientiane airport and one day before a bomb killed several
people at the central post office.
</P>
</TEXT>
