 &UR; ALZA _  &LR;  The U.S. Food and Drug Administration on Tuesday approved
a one-a-day pill for attention-deficit disorder that is easier to
take and possibly more effective than current three-a-day versions
of the commonly prescribed drug Ritalin.
</P>
<P>
