 &UR; ELECTRICITY _  &LR; Under pressure from Gov. Gray Davis and regulatory
agencies, the California Independent System Operator on Tuesday
slashed the maximum price it pays for wholesale power in half to
$250 per megawatt.
</P>
<P>
   It was the third time in a month that the board has taken action
to reduce the price cap from $750 per megawatt, as hot weather
triggered record customer demand and doubled energy bills in San
Diego.  &UR; BY KELLY YAMANOUCHI &LR;
